# Case 01 — BlackCat (ALPHV) Ransomware: Enterprise Outbreak Investigation

 Case ID:  DFIR-2024-001  
 Classification:  Critical  
 Investigator:  Himanshu Chourasia  
 Tools:  KAPE, Hayabusa, EZTools (MFTECmd, PECmd, RBCmd), CrowdStrike Falcon, Magnet AXIOM  
 Duration:  18 hours (initial triage → containment → root cause)

---

## Executive Summary

A mid-sized logistics firm (2,400 endpoints) suffered a BlackCat/ALPHV ransomware outbreak that encrypted 340 servers across three data centres over a 6-hour window. The threat actor gained initial access via a VPN appliance vulnerability (CVE-2023-46805 — Ivanti Connect Secure), established persistence using a scheduled task masquerading as a Windows update process, and conducted lateral movement via PsExec and stolen domain admin credentials before deploying the ransomware encryptor via GPO.

This report details the full attacker timeline, forensic artefacts recovered, TTPs mapped to MITRE ATT&CK, and recommendations to prevent recurrence.

